The Zondo Commission will continue to hear State Security Agency (SSA) related evidence from an unidentified witness at 10h00 on Friday JOHANNESBURG - State Security Agency (SSA) investigator -- known only as Ms K -- continues to present evidence. She is referring to a colleague, Mr Y’s affidavit. Ms K said at the start of her evidence that she and others probing corruption at the SSA have been threatened and intimidated. The true identities of Ms K and Mr Y have been unlawfully revealed. The commission heard further evidence on Thursday of how the agency’s resources were abused. The Special Operations Unit, led by Thulani Dlomo, incurred expenses of nearly R1-billion between 2012 and 2018.